(**Q3: Does the private layer change Atho's supply cap?**) Tj
T*
(No. The active chain still reaches exactly 1,000,000,000.00000 ATHO under the core fixed-point) Tj
T*
(decay schedule. PrivateTx changes transaction composition and cost behavior, not hard monetary) Tj
T*
(bounds.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q4: What are the most important operational controls?**) Tj
T*
(Pinned proving/verifying binaries, strict payload/proof bounds, deterministic rollback logic,) Tj
T*
(and synchronized docs/constants updates before release.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q5: Why does throughput decrease as private share increases?**) Tj
T*
(Private transactions carry larger payload and witness surfaces and require additional validation) Tj
T*
(work. That overhead is expected and is explicitly budgeted in policy and capacity planning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q6: How should teams evaluate readiness for production?**) Tj
T*
(Run full adversarial test vectors, verify apply/revert symmetry, validate binary pin metadata,) Tj
T*
(review congestion behavior, and confirm that doc claims map to active code paths.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q7: What is the most common integration mistake?**) Tj
T*
(Treating API convenience logic as if it were a validator guarantee. Client helpers are helpful,) Tj
T*
(but consensus correctness is always decided by validator path enforcement.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q8: Why include both technical and condensed papers?**) Tj
T*
(The technical paper supports implementation and audit depth. The condensed paper supports) Tj
T*
(investor and non-technical understanding while preserving alignment to the same baseline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q9: How are reorgs handled for private notes?**) Tj
T*
(Private notes, nullifiers, and anchor windows are reconciled via deterministic apply/revert) Tj
T*
(logic. Maturity and spendability are recomputed against canonical chain position.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Q10: What prevents cross-network replay of private material?**) Tj
T*
(Network-domain identifiers are bound into commitment, nullifier, and signing preimages so valid) Tj
T*
(material from one network does not validate on another.) Tj
